Start
/ A read of config.json lands the file as {item, json} (born-native: a json payload of
/ unknown shape is `item`). The critical lazy invariant: stamping `type=item` does NOT
/ parse — `%cfg%` untouched is still the raw json *string*. Materialisation only fires on
/ navigation (see ReadConfigJson_NavigateMaterialisesField). Requires the config.json
/ fixture committed alongside.
- read file 'config.json', write to %cfg%
- assert %cfg.Type.Name% equals "item"
- assert %cfg.Type.Kind% equals "json"
- assert %cfg% equals "{\"port\":8080}"
